dismissalText.commentary: Imam-ul-Haq run out (Patel) 10 (26b 0x4 0x6 48m) SR: 38.46

dismissalComment.html: Axar nails a direct hit from mid-on and Imam could be out here. Axar thinks he has his man. Indeed, he's gone. There was no single there. Signs of panic after dotting up? Imam jumps out of his crease once again and pushes it straight to Axar at mid-on. Axar gathers the ball quickly and throws down the stumps at the bowler's end to catch Imam well short. The belated dive isn't enough for Imam. Two in two overs for India

dismissalComment.html: Boundary and out! Hardik has Babar nicking this behind. Rahul dives to his right to grab the ball. He can only snick it behind to the keeper. Early breakthrough for India. Babar gone for 23 off 26 balls

dismissalText.commentary: Tayyab Tahir b Jadeja 4 (6b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Jaffa to dink off stump! And Jadeja knows it, skedaddles to the left, upper cuts the air while letting go a roar. Was a stock ball, landed on a length in front of middle and turned away a touch. Tahir was leg side of the ball, standing in front of leg. Front leg was out of the way - likely to avoid lbw - and tried to run it towards third. Tentative poke, got the wrist down but played the wrong line. Ball hit middle and off in the end, around top of the stumps. Pakistan's slump continues.

dismissalText.commentary: Tayyab Tahir b Jadeja 4 (6b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Jaffa to dink off stump! And Jadeja knows it, skedaddles to the left, upper cuts the air while letting go a roar. Was a stock ball, landed on a length in front of middle and turned away a touch. Tahir was leg side of the ball, standing in front of leg. Front leg was out of the way - likely to avoid lbw - and tried to run it towards third. Tentative poke, got the wrist down but played the wrong line. Ball hit middle and off in the end, around top of the stumps. Pakistan's slump continues.

dismissalComment.html: Whoa! Afridi storms back. He storms through the defences of Rohit with a ripping inswinging yorker. How do you play that? Magic ball from Afridi: on pace, very full, swings back in, swings back in late, against the angle from left-arm over to clatter into the middle stump. Rohit desperate jams his bat down but can't touch it. Rohit was lbw for duck in 2021 in Dubai. He's bowled for 20 at the same venue in 2025
